<dl id="s18016ac"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us18" href="#s18016ac">Penelope: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s18all.htm#s18016ac">sector 16(ac)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gun take down china, mirrors open window <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s18016ac"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/lext.htm#s18016ac">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/t86.htm#s18016ac">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/t86.htm#s18016ac">1986 (18.679f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/l22t.htm#s18016ac">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s18016ac">MS TS-B</ms> </li><li>JJA 16:319 </li><li><a name="td4" href="../udra/u18da.htm#td4">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/t/td4.htm#s18016ac">Draft: 18.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">As the house of the Major General stands on the Line-Wall, it is close to the enormous batteries in the casemates below, (while one of the hundred-ton guns is mounted near the Alameda, quite &ldquo;within speaking distance,&rdquo;) and must be rudely rocked by the thunder which shakes even the solid ground like an earthquake. &ldquo;What do you do at such a time?&rdquo; I asked of the ladies of the family, to which they answered gayly, &ldquo;Oh, we don&apos;t mind it.&rdquo; They took good care, however, <mark>to take down their mirrors, and to lay away their glass and china, lest they should be shattered in pieces. Then they threw open their windows</mark>, and let the explosion come. <small> Henry M. Field, <a name="HMFG" href="/udra/udex.htm#hmfg"><cite title="source">Gibralter</cite></a> (1888), p 60f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
